# Atlas — Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in the values. Do NOT commit .env.local.

# === Day 2: Clerk (Authentication) ===
# Get these from https://dashboard.clerk.com/
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_REPLACE_ME
CLERK_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_REPLACE_ME

# === Day 2: Supabase (Postgres + Auth) ===
# Get these from https://supabase.com/dashboard/project/_/settings/api
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://REPLACE_ME.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=sb_publishable_REPLACE_ME
SUPABASE_SECRET_KEY=sb_secret_REPLACE_ME

# === Day 2: Database (Supabase Postgres + Prisma) ===
# Get this from https://supabase.com/dashboard/project/_/settings/database
#
# IMPORTANT — Prisma + Supabase PgBouncer compatibility:
# Add ?pgbouncer=true to the DATABASE_URL query string. This tells Prisma
# to disable server-side prepared statements. Without it, Prisma collides
# with PgBouncer's transaction-mode pooler and throws:
#   "prepared statement \"s0\" already exists"  (Postgres error 42P05)
#
# Why: PgBouncer's transaction-mode pooler recycles the underlying Postgres
# session between transactions. Prisma's default behavior is to PREPARE a
# statement named "s0", "s1", ... on the first query and reuse it on the
# next one. When PgBouncer hands the recycled session to a different Vercel
# serverless invocation, that invocation tries to PREPARE "s0" again on a
# session that still owns it from the prior call → 42P05.
#
# The ?pgbouncer=true flag flips Prisma into a mode that does NOT use
# server-side prepared statements. Each query is sent unprepared, so there
# is nothing to collide with across pooler hand-offs. Slightly more
# network bytes per query, but the connection pool works as designed.
#
# Pooler choice — Supabase offers three connection modes on port 6543:
#   - "Transaction" pooler  (port 6543) — REQUIRES ?pgbouncer=true
#   - "Session"     pooler  (port 6543) — works WITH or WITHOUT ?pgbouncer=true
# Use the Transaction pooler for best Prisma + Vercel serverless behavior,
# with ?pgbouncer=true appended as shown below.
#
# Canonical URL pattern (copy this shape, fill in your project ref + password):
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres.PROJECT_REF:PASSWORD@aws-1-ap-southeast-1.pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres?pgbouncer=true"

# === Day 3: Model Registry (AI) ===
# Atlas supports a pluggable model registry. Each model is gated on its own
# env var. If the env var is not set, Atlas automatically falls back to the
# curated stub so the user never sees a 500.
#
# Default model is "gemini-flash" (set in /api/ask/route.ts when no model
# is provided in the request body).
#
# --- Google Gemini (default free tier) ---
# Get from https://aistudio.google.com/apikey  (free, no card required)
# Free tier: 15 RPM / 1500 RPD on gemini-1.5-flash.
GEMINI_API_KEY=AIzaSy_REPLACE_ME
#
# --- OpenRouter (free open-source models) ---
# Get from https://openrouter.ai/keys  (signup, free credits on signup)
# Used to serve the "llama-free" and "mistral-free" entries in the dropdown.
# Free tier per-model: 20 RPM / 50 RPD.
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-v1_REPLACE_ME
#
# --- OpenAI (paid, premium tier) ---
# Get from https://platform.openai.com/api-keys  ($5 free credit on signup)
# Used to serve the "gpt-4o-mini" and "gpt-4o" entries in the dropdown.
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-proj_REPLACE_ME
#
# --- (Removed in Day 3) Day 3 preview placeholder ---
# The previous placeholder was MINIMAX_API_KEY. Atlas now uses the registry
# pattern above. The MiniMax API key is no longer used by Atlas — Alex (the
# AI assistant running the build) is on MiniMax M3, but Atlas (the product)
# runs on the vendor models listed above.

# === Day 4: Mapbox (Maps) ===
# Get from https://account.mapbox.com/access-tokens/
# Mapbox free-tier: 50,000 map loads / month. The public token is
# client-side and scoped via Mapbox account → URL restrictions. The map
# will not render without this token set in Vercel env vars.
# Atlas /result/[id] reads this via process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_MAPBOX_TOKEN.
NEXT_PUBLIC_MAPBOX_TOKEN=pk.eyJ1_REPLACE_ME

# === Day 5: OpenStreetMap Overpass (Connectors) ===
# Atlas's first real connector. Overpass is public + free, no key required.
# Endpoint: https://overpass-api.de/api/interpreter  (POST form-encoded)
# Docs:     https://overpass-api.de/
# The connector lives in lib/connectors/overpass.ts and is enabled by default.
# No env var needed — if you want to point at a self-hosted Overpass mirror,
# change OVERPASS_URL at the top of lib/connectors/overpass.ts.

# === Week 2: Connector API keys ===
# Property24, Private Property, Google Places, CoinGecko, GitHub, Reddit, etc.

# === Day 12 v9: Google Street View (live site imagery) ===
# Used by components/StreetViewPanel.tsx to render a 640x360 jpeg
# for each ranked candidate site so users can eyeball the area
# without driving out. Same key works for both the Static Street
# View API and the Places API (the Google Cloud Console shows
# them under one project).
#
# Setup:
#   1. Open https://console.cloud.google.com/
#   2. Create a project (or pick an existing one).
#   3. Enable "Maps JavaScript API" + "Places API" (one project
#      covers all of them).
#   4. Create an API key under Credentials.
#   5. RESTRICT the key by HTTP referrer to:
#        atlas-q2eh.vercel.app/*
#        localhost:3000/*
#      Without this restriction, anyone who sees the key in the
#      HTML bundle can bill against your project. The key is in
#      NEXT_PUBLIC_ so it's exposed client-side.
#   6. Add to Vercel env vars for all 3 environments.
#
# Pricing: $7 per 1000 Static Street View requests. Free tier
# is $200/month credit = ~28,000 requests. At 5 sites per result
# and 100 results/day, that's ~15,000/month — within free tier.
#
# Graceful degrade: if the env var is missing, the Street View
# panel shows a setup hint instead of a broken image. The map
# and rest of the result page still work.
NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=AIzaSy_REPLACE_ME

# === Day 13: Stripe billing (Pro R250/mo + Team R2,500/mo) ===
# Atlas's pricing page has Subscribe buttons. They POST to
# /api/stripe/checkout which creates a Checkout Session. The
# user pays on Stripe, Stripe redirects them back, and the
# webhook updates their plan.
#
# Setup steps (one-time, 10 min):
#   1. Create a Stripe account at https://dashboard.stripe.com/register
#   2. Switch to "Test mode" (toggle in the top right)
#   3. Dashboard → Developers → API keys → Reveal test secret key
#   4. Copy "sk_test_..." → paste as STRIPE_SECRET_KEY below
#   5. Dashboard → Products → "Add product"
#      - Pro: Recurring, R250 ZAR / monthly → copy the price ID (price_...)
#      - Team: Recurring, R2,500 ZAR / monthly → copy the price ID
#   6. Paste the two price IDs below
#   7. Dashboard → Developers → Webhooks → "Add endpoint"
#      - URL: https://atlas-q2eh.vercel.app/api/stripe/webhook
#      - Events: checkout.session.completed, customer.subscription.deleted, customer.subscription.updated
#      - Reveal the signing secret (whsec_...) → paste as STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET below
#   8. All 3 env vars in all 3 environments (Production, Preview, Development)
#   9. When ready to go live: switch to "Live mode" in Stripe, repeat steps 3-7
#      with the live keys (sk_live_..., price_..., whsec_...)
#
# Without these keys, the Subscribe buttons gracefully fall back
# to /waitlist?plan=pro so David still captures intent.
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_REPLACE_ME
STRIPE_PRICE_PRO_MONTHLY=price_REPLACE_ME_PRO
STRIPE_PRICE_TEAM_MONTHLY=price_REPLACE_ME_TEAM
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_REPLACE_ME

# === Day 26: CoinGecko (crypto prices) ===
# /crypto page uses CoinGecko's public /coins/markets endpoint.
# Free tier works WITHOUT a key (rate-limited to ~10-30 req/min).
# The connector caches results for 5 minutes, so a single page
# load uses 1 quota slot. With 200 loads/day = 200 req = within
# free tier comfortably.
#
# Pro tier ($129/mo at coingecko.com/en/api/pricing) raises the
# limit and gives priority routing — useful once Atlas has real
# traffic on the /crypto page.
#
# Setup:
#   1. Sign up at https://www.coingecko.com/en/api (free, no card)
#   2. Dashboard → API Keys → copy the key
#   3. Add COINGECKO_API_KEY=<key> to all 3 Vercel envs
#   4. With key set, requests route through pro-api.coingecko.com
#      with higher rate limits.
COINGECKO_API_KEY=

# === Day 15: PayFast (SA-native payment gateway, recommended) ===
# PayFast is South Africa's leading payment gateway. It's the
# recommended payment processor for Atlas's SA wedge because:
#   - SA-native, sign up with SA ID number (no Stripe Atlas needed)
#   - No country restrictions on signup
#   - No business registration needed (use personal bank account)
#   - Supports credit card, Instant EFT, SnapScan, Zapper, Mobicred
#   - 2.9% + R2.00 per ZAR transaction
#   - Payouts to any SA bank (FNB, Absa, Standard Bank, etc)
#
# Atlas's PricingClient button tries Stripe first, then PayFast,
# then falls back to /waitlist. So even with Stripe not set up,
# PayFast subscriptions work end-to-end.
#
# Setup steps (one-time, 30 min):
#   1. Sign up at https://www.payfast.co.za
#      - Use your SA ID number (no business registration needed)
#      - Add a bank account (FNB, Absa, Standard Bank, etc)
#   2. Wait for PayFast to verify your ID + bank (1-2 business days)
#   3. Dashboard → Settings → Integration
#      - Copy Merchant ID → paste as PAYFAST_MERCHANT_ID below
#      - Copy Merchant Key → paste as PAYFAST_MERCHANT_KEY below
#      - Generate a passphrase → paste as PAYFAST_PASSPHRASE below
#   4. Set the ITN URL in PayFast dashboard:
#      - Dashboard → Settings → Integration → "Notify URL (ITN)"
#      - Set to: https://atlas-q2eh.vercel.app/api/payfast/itn
#   5. Test mode: use sandbox.payfast.co.za
#      - Sandbox merchant ID: 10000100
#      - Sandbox merchant key: 46f0cd694581a
#      - Sandbox passphrase: q1Uz2sB6
#      - Set PAYFAST_BASE_URL=https://sandbox.payfast.co.za for testing
#   6. Add the 3 env vars to all 3 Vercel environments
#   7. Test by clicking Subscribe on /pricing — should redirect to
#      PayFast's hosted checkout page
#
# David: this is the recommended path for the SA wedge. Sign up
# before Monday's cold emails so any Pro/Team signups are real.
PAYFAST_MERCHANT_ID=10000100
PAYFAST_MERCHANT_KEY=46f0cd694581a
PAYFAST_PASSPHRASE=q1Uz2sB6
PAYFAST_BASE_URL=https://sandbox.payfast.co.za

# === Day 13: Resend (waitlist + demo + contact emails) ===
# Every email Atlas sends goes to davidnkana74@gmail.com via
# the Resend API. Without RESEND_API_KEY, the email is logged
# to the Vercel server console and the user record is still
# persisted — admin dashboard is the source of truth.
#
# Setup (one-time, 2 min):
#   1. Sign up at https://resend.com (free, no card, 3,000/month)
#   2. Dashboard → API Keys → "Create API Key"
#   3. Copy "re_..." → paste as RESEND_API_KEY below in all 3 envs
#   4. (optional) Add + verify a custom domain to send from
#      atlas@yourdomain.com instead of onboarding@resend.dev
#
# To test: POST to /api/contact with a sample message, then
# check davidnkana74@gmail.com. (Or just hit /api/waitlist
# from the home page with a real email.)
RESEND_API_KEY=re_REPLACE_ME

# === Day 12 v23: Perplexity-style research models ===
#
# Atlas ships three research-grade models that produce Perplexity-style
# answers (prose summary + clickable citation list + ranked suburb
# list). They cascade in order:
#
#   1. gemini-search  — Gemini 2.5 Flash with Google Search grounding
#                       Uses ONLY the existing GEMINI_API_KEY. Free.
#   2. tavily         — Tavily web search + Gemini 1.5 Flash synthesis
#                       Needs TAVILY_API_KEY + GEMINI_API_KEY. Free.
#   3. perplexity     — Perplexity Sonar API (search + gen server-side)
#                       Needs PERPLEXITY_API_KEY. $5 free signup credit.
#
# If the user's first-pick model fails, the route cascades through
# these automatically. The user always sees a real research answer
# (or the curated stub if all three are exhausted).
#
# --- Tavily: 1,000 credits/month free, no card ---
#   1. Go to https://tavily.com/pricing
#   2. Click "Get Free API Key" — sign up with Google/email.
#   3. Dashboard → API Keys → "Create New Key"
#   4. Copy the key (starts with tvly-)
#   5. Add TAVILY_API_KEY=tvly-... to Vercel env vars for all 3 envs.
#   6. Atlas's lib/models/tavily.ts wires this automatically.
#
# --- Perplexity Sonar: $5 free signup credit, no card ---
#   1. Go to https://www.perplexity.ai/settings/api
#   2. Sign up with Google/email (free, no card).
#   3. Click "Generate" under API Keys.
#   4. Copy the key (starts with pplx-)
#   5. Add PERPLEXITY_API_KEY=pplx-... to Vercel env vars.
#   6. Atlas's lib/models/perplexity.ts wires this automatically.
#   7. ~$0.005-0.01 per search. $5 = 500-1000 searches.
#
# --- Gemini API key: may need to be rotated ---
# If the existing GEMINI_API_KEY (AQ.Ab8RN6...) is rate-limited,
# get a new one at https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
# The new key will start with "AIzaSy" (AI Studio) not "AQ.Ab8RN6"
# (Vertex AI). Add it to Vercel env as GEMINI_API_KEY.
#
# Set NEXT_PUBLIC_HAS_TAVILY=true|false and NEXT_PUBLIC_HAS_PERPLEXITY=
# true|false to control which models show in the picker as "available"
# in the browser. Server-side isAvailable() is authoritative.

# Wired one at a time in Week 2.

# === Day 23: NewsAPI.org (investor-relevant news feed) ===
# The /news page and the News sidebar tab pull articles filtered to
# stocks, crypto, investments, and real estate. SA-biased for land-
# development-relevant categories (stocks + real_estate).
#
# Free tier: 100 requests / day, no card required. With 1-hour
# in-memory cache, /news will use ~24 requests/day = ~24% of free tier.
#
# Setup (one-time, 2 min):
#   1. Sign up at https://newsapi.org/register (free, no card)
#   2. Dashboard → API Keys → copy the key
#   3. Add NEWS_API_KEY=<key> to all 3 Vercel environments
#   4. /api/news/diag will confirm wiring + return sample articles
#
# Graceful degrade: if NEWS_API_KEY is missing or quota exceeded,
# the /news page renders an empty state with a setup hint instead
# of breaking. No 500s.
NEWS_API_KEY=REPLACE_ME

# === LCP-50/51/52: Atlas Strategy (multi-source social signals) ===
# Powers /api/strategy/feed, /api/strategy/coin/[coin], /api/strategy/diag,
# /api/strategy/_test-connectors. All four connectors are server-only
# and gracefully degrade if their env var is missing.
#
# The Strategy product is a per-coin social momentum view. It pulls
# from CryptoPanic, YouTube, Reddit, and GitHub Activity. None of
# these env vars are required for the product to run — they're
# optional quality-of-life upgrades that raise rate limits and
# unlock full data depth.
#
# IMPORTANT: this file is .env.example, NOT .env.local. .env.local
# is gitignored and never committed. The values below are placeholder
# names only. Real keys go in Vercel dashboard env vars and your
# local .env.local.
#
# --- CryptoPanic: 200 req/day free (no key required) ---
#   1. Sign up at https://cryptopanic.com/developers/api/ (free)
#   2. Dashboard → API Keys → "Generate"
#   3. Copy the key
#   4. Add CRYPTOPANIC_API_KEY=<key> to all 3 Vercel envs
#   5. With key, free tier raises from 200 to 500 req/day. Pro is $49/mo.
CRYPTOPANIC_API_KEY=
#
# --- YouTube Data API v3: 10,000 units/day free, key REQUIRED ---
#   1. https://console.cloud.google.com/ → create/select project
#   2. APIs & Services → Library → "YouTube Data API v3" → Enable
#   3. APIs & Services → Credentials → "Create Credentials" → "API key"
#   4. RESTRICT the key to atlas-q2eh.vercel.app and localhost
#   5. Add YOUTUBE_API_KEY=<key> to all 3 Vercel envs
#   6. Without this key, the YouTube source returns empty (no-key status).
#      /strategy and /crypto Strategy surfaces show "YouTube unavailable".
YOUTUBE_API_KEY=
#
# --- Reddit OAuth2: 100 req/min with auth, anonymous works for dev ---
#   1. https://www.reddit.com/prefs/apps → "create app" → type "script"
#   2. Add "atlas-q2eh.vercel.app/api/strategy/feed" as redirect URI (not
#      strictly required for client-credentials flow, but Reddit's form
#      requires it)
#   3. Submit the Responsible Builder Policy form (answers in
#      docs/strategy/lcp-50-scope.md Section 2 / Reddit approval text)
#   4. Once approved, copy the client_id and client_secret
#   5. Add REDDIT_CLIENT_ID and REDDIT_CLIENT_SECRET to all 3 Vercel envs
#   6. Without these, Reddit connector runs in anonymous mode — works in
#      dev with descriptive User-Agent, but IP-rate-limited in production.
REDDIT_CLIENT_ID=
REDDIT_CLIENT_SECRET=
#
# --- GitHub Activity: 60 req/hr anonymous, 5,000 with token ---
#   1. GitHub → Settings → (scroll to bottom) → Developer settings
#   2. Personal access tokens → Tokens (classic) → "Generate new token"
#   3. Note: "Atlas Strategy data fetcher"
#   4. Expiration: 90 days (rotate as needed)
#   5. Scopes: leave ALL UNCHECKED — public data only, no private repo access
#   6. Copy the token (starts with ghp_)
#   7. Add GITHUB_TOKEN=<token> to all 3 Vercel envs
#   8. Without this token, GitHub source works on the 60 req/hr public
#      tier. With it, 5,000 req/hr. Token is unnecessary for MVP.
GITHUB_TOKEN=

# How to verify the Strategy pipeline end-to-end in production:
#   curl https://atlas-q2eh.vercel.app/api/strategy/diag
#   curl https://atlas-q2eh.vercel.app/api/strategy/_test-connectors
#   curl https://atlas-q2eh.vercel.app/api/strategy/feed?coin=bitcoin
#
# The diag endpoint NEVER returns key values, only envKeyPresent: true/false.
# The _test-connectors endpoint runs all four connectors bypassing cache
# and reports per-source latency, item count, sample data, and any error.
